# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — gwshield-images
# =============================================================================
# Build context is the repo root (required so shared/banner/ is reachable from
# every image Dockerfile). This file keeps the context lean by excluding
# everything that is not needed inside any image build.
#
# Rule: include only what Dockerfiles actually COPY.
#   - shared/banner/gwshield-init.c         (all images)
#   - images/<name>/<version>/configs/      (per-image config files)
#   - images/<name>/<version>/Dockerfile    (implicit — already the -f target)
#
# Everything else stays on the host.
# =============================================================================

# --- Version control ---
.git
.gitattributes
.gitignore

# --- IDE / editor ---
.idea
*.iml
.vscode

# --- Scan outputs, logs, secrets ---
*.log
*.json
trivy-results*
grype-results*
.trivyignore
.grype.yaml

# Explicitly keep what we need:
# (dockerignore has no "include" syntax — we exclude broad patterns above
#  and rely on the fact that shared/banner/gwshield-init.c is NOT excluded
#  by any of the above rules)
